# Locale and Routing Rules

- All user-facing pages must live under `app/[locale]/...`.
- Supported locales are `pt` and `en` only; validate locale before rendering.
- Internal links in page UI and nav must be locale-prefixed (e.g. `/${locale}/auth/register`).
- Do not hardcode mixed-language text in shared pages; read copy from dictionaries.
- Keep default redirect behavior from `/` to `/${defaultLocale}` via proxy.
- If adding a new page, provide translation keys in `lib/i18n/dictionaries.ts`.
